@joshrsmith If you need the ability to run a VUnit testbench within a simulator without the Python runner you should also include a default value for the `runner_cfg` generic.

``` vhdl
entity tb_example is
  generic (runner_cfg : runner_cfg_t  := runner_cfg_default);
end entity;
```

This default will run all test cases in your testbench. Be aware that they will run in the same simulation so there is a risk of dependencies causing test cases to fail although the problem is a side effect from a previously run test case.

